answer: No, the data does not support this trend. answer: The data suggests a potential correlation. The only plan that has 'shares to be issued if performance is achieved at maximum' (the 2016 plan) is also the only plan that expects to make new awards. Conversely, all plans that have zero performance-based shares do not expect to make new awards. This implies that active, modern plans may incorporate performance-based incentives, while older, inactive plans do not.
